Comment: Dear Governor Beverly Perdue: I am writing to you to express my deepest concern regarding the future of our local petroleum industry. The Obama Administration has proposed sweeping changes to the tax burden on the oil and gas industry that if enacted will significantly harm our area's oil and gas production industry, and the jobs and economic benefits that it brings to our local economies of southern Illinois, southwestern Indiana, and western Kentucky. Taxes aimed at the local oil and gas production industry are the repeal of the percentage depletion allowance, elimination of expensing of intangible drilling costs, elimination of the passive loss exception, and a change to the amortization schedule for geological and geophysical costs. Repeal of the Percentage Depletion Allowance alone will devastate the American oil and gas industry. If enacted, this proposal will not only result in an immediate and huge increase to our tax burden, but it will jeopardize the continued existence of economically marginal stripper wells that account for nearly all the production in the Illinois Basin. Percentage Depletion Allowance was established in 1926 and is available to companies who produce less than 1,000 barrels of oil per day. The proposed repeal of this provision is a direct attack on small independent producers and interest owners like us. The Obama administration has also proposed significantly raising taxes on America's oil refining companies. These "Carbon" taxes on gasoline and diesel fuel will increase energy costs significantly, by some estimates as much as $3000 per year per person. The higher energy taxes will also significantly increase the cost of operating the local farmer owned CountryMark oil refinery located in Mt. Vernon Indiana. This refinery buys most of the oil produced in our area. As one of the nation's smallest refineries, this refinery is much more vulnerable to higher taxes than those owned by the large oil companies. The higher tax structure threatens the 350 jobs at CountryMark, as well as hundreds more that depend upon the economic activity arising from the company's operations. In conclusion, I encourage you to oppose the Obama Administration's attack on American oil and gas industry. Eliminating longstanding tax code that encourages the responsible development of American energy, and adding carbon taxes to small refining companies such as CountryMark, will only increase our nation's reliance on foreign oil while destroying thousands of American jobs. In the Indiana area alone, it is estimated that more than 20,000 jobs are at stake and none of them work for "big oil". Sincerely, Ann Kurz 1404 Ventnor Pl Cary, NC 27519-6329

